          "correctOptionId": "opt-1",
          "explanation": "Ans.B. FluoxetinThis patient is suffering from obsessive-compulsive disorder (OCD). Preferentially Selective Serotonin Reuptake Inhibitors (SSRIs), the medications most effective in treating OCD, mainly inhibit their reuptake of serotonin into nerve cells. These medications include clomipramine, fluoxetine, seraline, paroxetine, citalopram, escitalopram, and fluvoxamine. Medications with noradrenergic reuptake inhibition produce no benefit and may counteract or diminish the efficacy of serotonergic reuptake inhibition."
