          "explanation": "Wernicke's encephalopathy - Long term use of alcohol lead to thiamine deficiency . Wernicke encephalopathy, caused by vitamin B1 deficiency, is not diagnosed in about 80% of cases. Classical triad Global confusion Ophthalmoplegia - m/c/c 6th nerve palsy Ataxias After thiamine therapy 1st one to improve is ophthalmoplegia followed by global confusion",
