          "correctOptionId": "opt-1",
          "explanation": "Wernicke - Korsakoff syndrome (WKS) is due to deficiency of thiamine which can be precipitated by chronic alcoholism (most common), malnutrition (marasmus) due to prolonged starvation, hyperemesis gravidarum, HIV - AIDS, bariatric surgery, hemodialysis for CRF, prolonged intravenous hyperalimentation, and malignancies (gastric carcinoma).\n\nNote - It is chronic alcohol abuse that causes WKS (not alcohol withdrawal) :- option b."
