          "correctOptionId": "opt-2",
          "explanation": "History of use of a typical antipsychotic followed by symptoms of high-grade fever, rigidity and increase CPK levels and leucocytosis is suggestive of Neuroleptic malignant syndrome (NMS). The patients with NMS may develop rhabdomyolysis, resulting in myoglobinuria and that may cause acute renal failure",
          "hint": "Topic: Schizophrenia Spectrum and Other Psychotic Disorders"
