          "correctOptionId": "opt-2",
          "explanation": "Cluster B consists of disorders considered \"dramatic, emotional and erratic\" and on a \"psychopathic continuum\". They have dramatic, impulsive and erratic features. There are 4 disorders that are classified under cluster B. It includes Antisocial (or Dissocial), Histrionic, and Borderline (or Emotionally Unstable) personality disorders. Ref: A Sho Textbook of Psychiatry, Niraj Ahuja, 7th Edition, pg. no. 113 Kaplan and sadock synopsis of psychiatry, 11th edition, page no.742",
          "hint": "Topic: Personality disorders"
