          "correctOptionId": "opt-1",
          "explanation": "Perioral movement after antipsychotic therapy occurs in two syndromes:-\n\n\nTardive dyskinesia → Facial muscles (perioral muscles) show involuntary movement.\nRabbit syndrome → Perioral tremor.\n\n\nPerioral muscles are also involved in acute dystonia, but there is a spasm of muscles (not movement) and it occurs within a week after initiation of the drug."
