          "explanation": "Fever, rigidity, excessive sweating, confusion, autonomic instability (labile BP), tachycardia, increased CPK and leucocytosis, in a patient on antipsychotic (Haloperidol), suggest the diagnosis of the neuroleptic malignant syndrome."
