          "explanation": "A i.e. Attention deficit hyperactivity disorderAutismAttention Deficit DisorderConduct DisorderThere is marked impairment ofreciprocal social & interpersonalinteractionMore common in males, the onsetoccurs before the age of 7 years,characterised, by:There is violation of rights and rules like- Frequent lying- Stealing or robbery- Absence of social smile- Poor attention span with- Running away from home & school- Absence of feardistractibility- Physical violence- Lack of attachment to- Hyperactivity- Crueltyparents and absence of- Impulsivity seperation anxiety- Moving about here and there - Lack of friends- Talks excessively - Solitary behaviour"
