          "correctOptionId": "opt-1",
          "explanation": "This is a case of lithium toxicity so next best management is to measure lithium levels. Signs of Lithium toxicity Dehydration, low sodium diet, renal impairment- precipitates lithium toxicity Narrow TI (>1.5 mEq/dL) GI symptoms-Abdominal pain, vomiting CNS : Coarse tremors, ataxia, dysahria Muscle fasciculations, increased DTR, convulsions, impaired consciousness, death Management: Stop LITHIUM Correct dehydration Use of sodium polystyrene sulfonate or polyethylene glycol (to remove unabsorbed lithium from GI) Hemodialysis (in severe cases)",
          "hint": "Topic: NEET Jan 2020"
